name: Corr Totem #1
description:
"For the Corr, it is an honor to have parts of their body become, over the years, the substance from which they build their shrines. Initially only adornment and embellishment, over the millennia it manifested as a custom to reserve for this ritual for the high priests of the deity Sut. Therefore devoting themselves entirely to the task of turning into totems. When their last heartbeat is done and their last thought has vanished, their countenances henceforth whisper the truths of the goddess for all eternity."

Excerpt from "Zeon – Observations of Another World"

*****
#####
Raiko Oldenettel
(2021, Ink on Paper, Digitally Enhanced)
